DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Abnormal Lymphocyte Result Percentage Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the percentage of infiltration by abnormal lymphocytes in a tissue sample or specimen.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of a medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood from the body for an atypical or abnormal lymphocyte, a type of white blood cell that fights infection and diseases._Deviating in any way from the state, position, structure, condition, behavior, or rule which is considered a norm._White blood cells formed in the body's lymphoid tissue. The nucleus is round or ovoid with coarse, irregularly clumped chromatin while the cytoplasm is typically pale blue with azurophilic (if any) granules. Most lymphocytes can be classified as either T or B (with subpopulations of each); those with characteristics of neither major class are called null cells.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: Deviating from the norm.:(LIM-fo-site) A type of white blood cell. Lymphocytes have a number of roles in the immune system, including the production of antibodies and other substances that fight infection and diseases.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: Deviating in any way from the state, position, structure, condition, behavior, or rule which is considered a norm.

White blood cells formed in the body's lymphoid tissue. The nucleus is round or ovoid with coarse, irregularly clumped chromatin while the cytoplasm is typically pale blue with azurophilic (if any) granules. Most lymphocytes can be classified as either T or B (with subpopulations of each); those with characteristics of neither major class are called null cells.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Integer value expressed as numbers up to 3 characters with no decimal place.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: Number; a concept of quantity derived from zero and units; a numeral or string of numerals that is used for identification.

Concepts.definition: A numeral or string of numerals expressing value, quantity, or identification.
